<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">
A m8 of mine pointed me in the direction of this lot.<P><A HREF="http://www.dynu.com/default.asp" TARGET=_blank>http://www.dynu.com/default.asp</A><P>Basically your register a sub-domain name with them, and a bit of software on your PC monitors your IP address, and updates the DNS entry on their DNS servers. So it means if you want to run a server of some kind, but your IP address keeps changing, then this solves the problem because you can always get to your computer via yourname.dynu.com. He has used it with his IDSN line, which gets a different address every time he connects. CM users could use it to avoid problems if their ISP keeps assigning differents IPs.
</FONT>
